<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>in my <code>/etc/enviroment</code></p> <p><code> QT_STYLE_OVERRIDE=kvantum QT_QPA_PLATFORM=wayland </code> In the Kvantum manager, I choose them I want. Even log out or reboot, the shotcut theme is not changed.</p> <p>my desktop is Gnome, I have tried to use <code>QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=qt5ct</code> with qt5ct and <code>QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=gnome</code> with qgnomeplatform-qt5, things are also not changed.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/malacokuoi"> /u/malacokuoi </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wiu6j0/kvantum_manager_doesnt_change_the_theme_under/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wiu6j0/kvantum_manager_doesnt_change_the_theme_under/">[comments]</a></span>